://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27481.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Ma$$ Group Buff (MGB) aa</span><hr size=1> What are your thoughts on this ability. Is it worth it? What requests do you get for the most part? Being that it uses up double mana I would presume it is nice but just curious for those that have this ability<br>
<br>
subject should read Mass group buff not sure why it read as it does <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uscirocco.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Scirocco</A> at: 6/2/02 6:04:39 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uscirocco.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Scirocco</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>FAQ/Index Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 5093<br> <font color=#333399>(6/2/02 9:09:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27481.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ma$$ Group Buff (MGB) aa</span><hr size=1> Not worth it.   We have three group buffs that would qualify: PoG, RoG, and Circle of Seasons.<br>
<br>
No raid wants PoG on everyone.  At most, you're going to cast it one or two times on caster groups.  More likely, you'll be raining Vegetable Justice (Cabbage) on casters individually.<br>
<br>
RoG might be worth it, but with a couple of druids with Velious BPs, you have it covered for no mana.  Also, keep in mind that shaman have a better RoG now.<br>
<br>
Circles you don't always need. In any event, it is long lasting and relatively low cost, so when you do need to hit several groups, you just target the leader and cast.<br>
<br>
In other words, it's really not worth the AA points unless you have everything else. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uhappyfeetfunkmaster.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Happyfeet Funkmaster</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 159<br> <font color=#333399>(6/2/02 10:26:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27481.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ma$$ Group Buff (MGB) aa</span><hr size=1> If your guild spends a ton of time in TOV(north or farming armor) MGB might be a good investment for AE COS...but I would hope that you all do other things than TOV, so it is probably pretty useless. <p>Happyfeet Funkmaster - Halfling Druid Extraordinaire 
<a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=164501>My Profile</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uspuzy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Spuzy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 18<br> <font color=#333399>(6/2/02 10:36:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27481.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ma$$ Group Buff (MGB) aa</span><hr size=1> Only time I found MGB to be usefull is at the High Priest in Ssraeshza Temple and that's simply because he overwrites AEGO with some sort of AE so everyone gets PoTG and Marzin for that fight.  Other then that, everyone gets AEGO aside from a few Wizards.  MGB Circle of Seasons?  Waste if you ask me, doesn't cost that much mana to cast it on x groups, and I'm sure you have at least more then one Druid around.  <br>
