tle> Re: Ma$$ Group Buff (MGB) aa</span><hr size=1> We won't mention the bigger edge that shaman have if you start including shaman spells in the picture...:) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umissfoxfyre.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Miss Foxfyre</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Administrator</span><br>  Posts: 1620<br> <font color=#333399>(6/2/02 7:04:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27481.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://gwynhyfar.homestead.com/files/hm9.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ma$$ Group Buff (MGB) aa</span><hr size=1> Well if you ask me, shamans are favored by VI and druids are not.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ulotusflystewnicely.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lotusfly Stewnicely</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 737<br> <font color=#333399>(6/2/02 7:42:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27481.topic&index=11>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.keepersofthefaith.org/images/snap.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Area of Effect</span><hr size=1> I think that this very much depends on your guild.<br>
<br>
My guild uses Marzin's Mark and PotG for all encounters; 95% of the fights that we go through, I'm the only druid able to AE.   Having another druid with this skill would provide a ton of versatility.<br>
<br>
When we're re-trying after a wipe-out on something new and nasty, or buffing quickly before a run with a new set of people, the shamen and clerics are all fine - there's always two or three of them online with MGB, so Marzin's Mark and Focus/Stamina are covered every time; there's always a shaman or cleric available with the skill up at any given time.<br>
<br>
Not so with druids; I'm not sure if it's just Prexus, but druids have a very, very low AA count compared to other classes.  You can take that for whatever you wish (class whines elsewhere), but the MGB skill is something that I use each and every raid.<br>
<br>
If your guild uses Blessing of Aegolism, the druid MGB skill is virtually useless.  I had the skill just before Christmas, and was using it on raids for one week until the first cleric got the skill, then we were using AE Aegolism for a while.  Once our clerics were equipped with Marzin's Mark, the situation reverted back to me AEing every raid.<br>
<br>
I'm certain that it's not the same in other guilds, as one can tell from reading the opinions above.  PotG + Marzin's Mark provides more hit points, so we use them.  If your guild doesn't have the MM spell, I can see where you'd come to the conclusion that it's not useful for you... but remember that's just for you, not for everyone. ^_^<br>
<br>
Of course, Ancient Blessing of Aegolism would mean that druids don't AE any more, but that's not around currently. ;)<br>
<br>
Guilds without Bless of Aegolism, druids AE.<br>
Guilds that have Blessing of Aegolism but no Marzin's Mark, druids don't AE.<br>
Guilds that have Marzin's Mark, druids AE again,<br>
<br>
No comment on Ancient Aego. ^_^<br>
<br>
On the 5% of occassions upon which we do have another MGB druid, and we're sure that we won't need to 'save' an MGB, I sometimes AE a RotG - with SCR Mastery, it lasts through the majority of encounters with which we play around.<br>
<br>
Casting Group Skin-Like-Wood after a wipeout is rather amusing, too, if you're on the last fight of the evening. ^_^<br>
<br>
<br>
